# Claude Memory — Dispatch Table

Read this first. It tells you exactly which file to load or write to — no need to read everything.

## Load by session type

| Session / Alias | Load these files |
|---|---|
| Any session | `core.md` |
| `<your-project-alias>` | `core.md` + `tooling.md` + `session_<project>.md` |

## Save by topic

| What you learned | Write to |
|---|---|
| Domain fix / rule | `brain-sync` → `<Domain>-Mistakes.md` |
| General code fix | `brain-sync` → `General-Mistakes.md` |
| User preference / behavior | `core.md` |
| Alias / CLI / tooling | `tooling.md` |
| Project-specific update | `session_<project>.md` |
| General coding rules | `session_general.md` |
| New agent rule | `AGENTS.md` |
| Session summary (human) | `Personal/Daily-Logs/YYYY-MM-DD.md` |

## File index

- [core.md](core.md) — your profile, speed mode, save rule + routing table
- [tooling.md](tooling.md) — aliases, CLI gotchas, handoff workflow
- `session_<project>.md` — one file per active project, created as needed
- `feedback_*.md` — one file per recurring behavior-correction topic, created as needed
